    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-predicate">
            <h>predicate</h>
            <p>Like other adjectives, <g>trang</g> can be used (uninflected) as the predicate of the
                verb <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a>
                <en>be</en>.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha Màiri agus Calum <m>trang</m> an diugh.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary and Malcolm are busy today.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Bha sinn <m>trang</m> ag obair.</gd>
                        <tr>We were busy working.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 9 [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>An robh sibh <m>trang</m>? Bha.</gd>
                        <tr>Were you busy? Yes, we were.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [227] [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>

